Sliding Window Approach:
i)Subarrays
ii)Substrings
iii)Continuous Range

A range - window - subsets of elements - 
We maintain a window(subset) of elements and move it step-by-step 
across the array/string, adjusting what changes.

Types:
i)fixed-sized window: the window size is fixed.
ii)variable-sized window: Windows size expands or shrinks based on 
condition.

Maximum size subarray of size k

arr=[2,1,5,1,3,2]

Possible subarrays of size k = 3

{2,1,5}  - 8
{1,5,1}  - 7
{5,1,3}  - 9
{1,3,2}  - 6



